  "text": "• Pink disease: Acrodynia (pink disease) occurs in children exposed to mercury for prolonged periods [CITATION_1] . Affected patients are initially listless, anorexic, and irritable. Their blood pressure and heart rate increase. Significant pain occurs in the hands and feet preventing sleep. Finally the hands and feet will swell and become paresthetic, becoming a dusky pink color along with a similar process which occurs in the nose [CITATION_2] .",
